The Edo State Governor, Mr. Godwin Obaseki, has mourned the demise of the Chairman of the Edo State Chapter of the Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC), Comrade Sunny Osayande. In a statement, Obaseki noted that the state was in great grief over the loss of a true comrade and icon of the Nigerian labour movement, whose selfless role in the maintenance of industrial harmony in Edo State will remain evergreen. The governor hailed the forthrightness of late Osayande, noting that he maintained a calm and balanced disposition towards the government whenever labour disputes arose in the state. Stop Inflicting Hardship On Nigerians, NDYCN Cautions FG Foreign Group To Renovate Olumirin Water Fall To Boost Osun… He said this positive disposition made the transformation exercise in the state’s public and civil service seamless. The governor commiserates with all workers in the state, the leadership and members of the NLC as well as the family and friends of late Comrade Osayande. He prayed to God Almighty to grant the soul of the departed labour leader eternal rest. Comrade Sunny Osayande passed on in the early hours of Sunday. Until his death, he was the Chairman of the Edo State Chapter of the Nigerian Labour Congress and was elected on April 25, 2019.